Hello,

Yes, you can add a bean like this to the end of the disposition chain:

     &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.crawler.postprocessor.ReschedulingProcessor&quot;&gt;
         &lt;property name=&quot;rescheduleDelaySeconds&quot; value=&quot;21600&quot; /&gt;
     &lt;/bean&gt;

You can use sheet overlays to apply different delays to different urls, or write a custom processor to reschedule (or not) according to an arbitrary algorithm. See also
https://webarchive.jira.com/wiki/display/Heritrix/H3+Dev+Notes+for+Crawl+Operators#H3DevNotesforCrawlOperators-FixedRescheduling

Noah


